SITE REMEDIATION CASE STUDIES

This (Federal Remediation Technologies Roundtable)
report is a collection of abstracts summarizing 37 case
studies of site remediation projects prepared by
federal agencies.  The case studies were undertaken to
document the results and lessons learned from early
technology applications.  They help to establish
benchmark data on cost and performance, which should
lead to greater confidence in the selection and use of
cleanup technologies.

