climate change-related research is five times greater than it was
in 1989.  Much of the growth can be attributed to redefinitions
and shifts of existing programs to fall under the "global change"
umbrella.  A total of $664 million will be available, with the
Department of Energy getting the biggest relative increase ($60
million).  Most of the funding ($489 million of it) sits with the
National Aeronautics and Space Administration.
     Call the GECR Hotline at +1-617-648-8700 for more
information on any news items covered in this issue.



